import Mathlib

open Complex

/-- Define the complex arctan via the principal logarithm. -/
def arctan (z : ‚ÑÇ) : ‚ÑÇ := (I / 2) * Complex.log ((I + z) / (I - z))

/-- If the principal branch of arctan is differentiable at z, its derivative equals 1 / (1 + z^2). -/
theorem hasDerivAt_arctan {z : ‚ÑÇ} (h : DifferentiableAt ‚ÑÇ arctan z) :
  HasDerivAt arctan (1 / (1 + z ^ 2)) z := by sorry

/-- If the principal branch of the complex logarithm is differentiable at z, its derivative equals 1 / z. -/
theorem hasDerivAt_log {z : ‚ÑÇ} (h : DifferentiableAt ‚ÑÇ Complex.log z) :
  HasDerivAt Complex.log (1 / z) z := by sorry

import Mathlib

open Complex

noncomputable def arctan_complex (z : ‚ÑÇ) : ‚ÑÇ := (I / 2) * Complex.log ((I + z) / (I - z))

/-- If the principal branch of arctan (defined via the principal log) is differentiable at z,
its derivative equals 1 / (1 + z^2). -/
theorem hasDerivAt_arctan_complex {z : ‚ÑÇ} (h : DifferentiableAt ‚ÑÇ arctan_complex z) :
  HasDerivAt arctan_complex (1 / (1 + z ^ 2)) z := by sorry

/-- If the principal branch of the complex logarithm is differentiable at z, its derivative equals 1 / z. -/
theorem hasDerivAt_log {z : ‚ÑÇ} (h : DifferentiableAt ‚ÑÇ Complex.log z) :
  HasDerivAt Complex.log (1 / z) z := by sorry
